OL,3,CEnergy companies to be forced to offer
OL,4,Clow or no standing charge tariffs
OL,6,F"The costs included in the standing
OL,7,Fcharge ultimately have to be paid. But
OL,8,Fwhile they may not save everyone
OL,9,Fmoney, they will give people a choice,
OL,10,Fand greater control over their bills."
OL,12,FThe consultation comes after Energy
OL,13,FSecretary Ed Miliband urged Ofgem to
OL,14,Fcrack down on rising costs.
OL,16,FRecent forecasts show that the amount
OL,17,Fpeople will pay per unit of
OL,18,Felectricity is set to go up again in
OL,19,FApril, even if most people's bills
OL,20,Fwill go down because of less usage.
