OL,3,CEnergy companies to be forced to offer
OL,4,Clow or no standing charge tariffs
OL,6,FMartin Lewis, founder of
OL,7,FMoneySavingExpert.com, said: "This is
OL,8,Fprogress. Standing charges are by far
OL,9,Fthe most complained-about part of an
OL,10,Fenergy bill.
OL,12,F"It costs in excess of #300 a year
OL,13,Fjust to have the facility of gas and
OL,14,Felectricity, even if you don't use any.
OL,16,F"They're a moral hazard that
OL,17,Fdisincentives lower users from cutting
OL,18,Ftheir bills, and leaves many older
OL,19,Fpeople, who only use gas for heating
OL,20,Fin the winter, still paying for it
OL,21,Fevery day in summer."
